.TH MOUNTFILE 8 "2026-05-06" "pfs-utils5" "PuppyRus PFS Module Tools"
.SH NAME
mountfile \- mount a filesystem image file at a given mount point
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mountfile
\fIFILE\fR
[\fIMOUNTPOINT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mountfile
mounts a filesystem image
.I FILE
using the filesystem type detected from its magic bytes.
Supported types include ext2, ext3, ext4, squashfs, ISO 9660, and erofs.
.PP
If
.I MOUNTPOINT
is not given,
.B mountfile
derives one automatically from the file path:
.RS
.nf
/mnt/<path-with-slashes-replaced-by-plus>
.fi
.RE
.PP
The mount point is created if it does not exist.
If the derived mount point already exists and is in use,
.B mountfile
exits with an error.
.PP
.B mountfile
prefers
.BR mount (8)
from util-linux.
On legacy environments without util-linux,
it falls back to
.BR busybox (1)
mount.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I FILE
Path to the filesystem image to mount.
.TP
.I MOUNTPOINT
Optional explicit mount point.
Created if it does not exist.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Mount a squashfs module at an auto-derived path:
.RS
.nf
mountfile /srv/modules/myapp.pfs
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mount at an explicit path:
.RS
.nf
mountfile /srv/modules/myapp.pfs /mnt/myapp
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
File not found, filesystem type not supported, or
.B mount
not available.
.PP
Other codes propagate from
.BR mount (8).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pfsload (8),
.BR pfs\-utils (8),
.BR mount (8)
.SH AUTHORS
PuppyRus pfs-utils maintainers.
